public class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        // A negative number cannot be a power of three
        if (n <= 0) {
            return false;
        }

        // A power of three always has 1 as its logarithm base 3
        // We use the Math.log function to calculate the logarithm
        // If the logarithm is an integer, then the number is a power of three
        return Math.log(n) / Math.log(3) % 1 == 0;
    }
}
```

This solution works because the logarithm base 3 of a power of three will always be an integer. Therefore, if the logarithm base 3 of a number is an integer, then that number is a power of three. The `Math.log` function calculates the natural logarithm of a number, and the `Math.log(3)` function calculates the logarithm base 3 of 3, which is a constant. The `% 1 == 0` part checks if the logarithm is an integer.

